Acid house.label: Acid house
Acid house.description: Acid house is a sub-genre of house music developed around the mid-1980s by DJs from Chicago, Illinois. The defining feature of a 'squelching' bass sound was produced using the Roland TB-303 electronic synthesizer-sequencer. Wikipedia

Acid rock.label: Acid rock
Acid rock.description: Acid rock is a form of psychedelic rock, which is characterized by long instrumental solos, few lyrics, and musical improvisation. Wikipedia

Bluegrass music.label: Bluegrass
Bluegrass music.description: Bluegrass music is a form of American roots music, and a sub-genre of country music. Bluegrass was inspired by the music of Appalachia. Wikipedia

Chopped and screwed.label: Chopped and screwed
Chopped and screwed.description: Chopped and screwed refers to a technique of remixing hip hop music which developed in the Houston hip hop scene in the 1990s. Wikipedia

Digital hardcore.label: Digital hardcore
Digital hardcore.description: Digital hardcore is a music genre that melds hardcore punk with electronic music such as hardcore techno, industrial and drum and bass. Wikipedia

Euro disco.label: Euro disco
Euro disco.description: Euro disco is the variety of European forms of electronic dance music that first originated from disco in the 1970s; incorporating elements of pop, new wave and rock into a disco-like continuous dance atmosphere. Wikipedia

Son montuno.label: Son montuno
Son montuno.description: The son montuno is a sub-genre of Son Cubano. The son itself is the most important genre of Cuban popular music. Wikipedia

Soul jazz.label: Soul Jazz Records
Soul jazz.description: Soul Jazz Records is a British record label based in London. The label started in the 1992 as a means to draw "cross cultural connections between various music genres". Wikipedia

Acid jazz.label: Acid jazz
Acid jazz.description: Acid jazz, also known as club jazz, is a musical genre that combines elements of jazz, soul, funk, disco and hip-hop. Wikipedia
